    title: "Getting Started with the SEO & Marketing Hub",
    slug: "getting-started-seo-marketing-hub",
    excerpt: "Your quick-start guide to setting up your account, adding your first website, and navigating the platform's core features.",
    content: `<h2>Welcome to Your Marketing Command Center</h2><p>This platform brings together all the SEO and marketing tools you need in a single workspace. You can track keyword rankings, monitor backlinks, manage social media campaigns, generate leads, and analyze performance — all without switching between multiple tools.</p><h2>Step 1: Add Your First Website</h2><p>Navigate to the Websites section and click "Add Website." Enter your domain name, choose your target country and language, and set your primary competitors. The platform will immediately begin gathering baseline data about your site's current performance.</p><h2>Step 2: Connect Google Search Console</h2><p>For the richest keyword and indexing data, connect your Google Search Console account via the Settings page. This integration imports your real click, impression, and ranking data directly from Google, supplementing our platform's own tracking.</p><h2>Step 3: Explore the Dashboard</h2><p>Your dashboard shows a summary of all your key metrics: total keywords tracked, ranking distribution, backlinks acquired, social posts scheduled, and lead activity. Bookmark the pages you'll visit daily and customize your dashboard widgets to surface the metrics most important to your goals.</p><ul><li>Use the left sidebar to navigate between modules</li><li>Click any metric card to see detailed breakdowns</li><li>Use the date picker at the top right to compare time periods</li><li>Access settings and account management from the top right avatar menu</li></ul>`,
