    content: `<h2>Adding Your Website</h2><p>From the Websites section, click "Add Website" to open the configuration form. Enter your full domain including the protocol (https://example.com). The platform supports multiple websites under a single account — add one for each domain you manage.</p><h2>Website Configuration Options</h2><p>After adding your website, configure these key settings: <strong>Target Geography</strong> — select the country and city where most of your target audience is located (affects rank tracking localization). <strong>Target Language</strong> — select the language your content is in. <strong>Competitors</strong> — add up to 5 competitor domains to track in comparison with your own rankings. <strong>Tags</strong> — add tags to organize multiple websites (e.g., "client site," "e-commerce," "blog").</p><h2>Verifying Your Site</h2><p>Some advanced features require website verification. The platform supports two verification methods: DNS TXT record (add a specific TXT record to your domain's DNS settings) or meta tag verification (add a specific meta tag to your homepage's HTML head section). Your hosting provider or developer can assist with DNS verification if needed.</p>`,
