    slug: "inviting-team-members-managing-permissions",
    excerpt: "Learn how to add staff accounts, assign module-level permissions, and manage your team's access to the platform's features.",
    content: `<h2>Adding Staff Accounts</h2><p>Admins can add staff accounts from the Admin section (accessible to admin users from the sidebar). Navigate to Admin → Staff Accounts → Add Staff Account. Enter a username, password, and role: Admin (full platform access) or Staff (granular permission control).</p><h2>Configuring Module Permissions</h2><p>For Staff accounts, you can enable or disable access to individual platform modules: Websites, Keywords, Social Media, Calendar, Campaigns, Backlinks, Leads, Conversations, Analytics, AI Tools, and Media Library. Staff with no permissions selected have full access to all modules (equivalent to admin minus admin-specific settings). Staff with specific modules selected can only access those modules — other sections show an Access Denied page.</p><h2>Managing Existing Staff</h2><p>View all staff accounts in the Admin panel's Staff tab. Click the expand arrow on any staff row to see their current permissions and edit them. Changes take effect the next time the staff member logs in — active sessions use the permissions from their existing login token. To remove a staff member, click the delete button on their row — their account will be permanently deleted and they will immediately lose platform access.</p>`,
