    excerpt: "Step-by-step guide to linking your Google Search Console account for enriched keyword data, indexing reports, and direct Google performance metrics.",
    content: `<h2>Why Connect Google Search Console?</h2><p>Google Search Console integration enriches the platform with first-party data directly from Google: the actual queries your pages rank for, real click-through rates, impression data, and indexing status. This data supplements our platform's own rank tracking with Google's own measurements — providing the most accurate possible picture of your search performance.</p><h2>Connecting Your Account</h2><p>Navigate to Settings → Integrations → Google Search Console. Click "Connect Google Account" and authenticate with the Google account that has access to your Search Console property. After authentication, select which Search Console property to connect to the current website in the platform. The integration will begin importing up to 16 months of historical performance data.</p><h2>What Data Is Imported</h2><p>After connection, you'll see enriched data in: the Keywords section (actual GSC query data alongside our rank tracking data), the Websites section (indexing status and Core Web Vitals data), and the Analytics section (organic performance charts using GSC data for maximum accuracy). Data refreshes daily, with up to a 3-day lag from Google's systems (GSC data is never real-time).</p>`,
