    excerpt: "Import your historical keyword rankings, backlink data, and contact lists from other tools or spreadsheets to hit the ground running with existing data.",
    content: `<h2>Supported Import Formats</h2><p>The platform accepts CSV imports for: Keywords (with optional columns for target URL, group, and current ranking), Backlinks (source URL, target URL, anchor text, and first seen date), Leads and Contacts (name, email, company, status, and custom fields), and Social Media Posts (platform, content, scheduled date). Download the import template for each data type from the import dialog to ensure your spreadsheet matches the expected format.</p><h2>Importing Keywords</h2><p>Navigate to Keywords → Import Keywords. Upload a CSV with your keyword list. Map the CSV columns to the platform's fields. Review the preview showing how your data will import, then confirm. Large imports (1,000+ keywords) may take several minutes to process — you'll receive a notification when the import is complete.</p><h2>Importing Leads</h2><p>Navigate to Leads → Import Leads. The import accepts standard CRM export formats from Salesforce, HubSpot, Pipedrive, and most other CRMs. Map your fields carefully — in particular, ensure email addresses import to the correct field to prevent duplicates. The platform automatically deduplicates imports based on email address — existing contacts with the same email are updated rather than duplicated.</p>`,
