    slug: "setting-up-white-label-reports-clients",
    excerpt: "Configure your branding and generate professional client reports that present your platform data under your own brand identity.",
    content: `<h2>White-Label Report Configuration</h2><p>Access report branding settings in Settings → Report Branding. Upload your logo, configure your brand colors, and add your agency's name and contact information. These settings apply globally to all reports generated from your account.</p><h2>Generating Client Reports</h2><p>Navigate to any website and click "Generate Report" to create a branded performance report. Configure what to include: ranking overview, position changes, backlink growth, traffic metrics, and custom notes or recommendations. Reports are generated as PDF documents suitable for sending to clients directly.</p><h2>Scheduling Recurring Reports</h2><p>Set up automated monthly or weekly reports that are generated and emailed to specified addresses automatically. Navigate to Settings → Report Scheduling to configure: which websites to include, report recipients (email addresses), frequency (weekly on Monday, monthly on the 1st), and the report sections to include. Automated reports ensure clients receive consistent updates without manual effort from your team.</p>`,
    category: "Getting Started",
    subcategory: "Reporting",
    tags: ["reporting", "white-label", "client reports", "pdf reports"],
