    content: `<h2>Starting with the AI Content Generator</h2><p>Navigate to AI Tools → Content Generator. The generator produces structured content drafts optimized for search. Input your target keyword, select your content type (blog post, landing page copy, product description), and specify any additional context: target audience, tone of voice, specific points to cover, and approximate target word count.</p><h2>Generating and Reviewing Drafts</h2><p>The AI generates a structured draft with H1 title, introduction, H2 sections with supporting content, and a conclusion. Review the draft critically: verify all factual claims (AI can hallucinate statistics — always fact-check), add your unique insights and first-hand expertise that the AI can't provide, and refine the tone to match your brand voice. The draft is a starting point requiring human expertise to reach publication quality — expect to spend 30–60 minutes refining a generated draft to your standards.</p><h2>SEO Optimization Features</h2><p>After generating content, use the SEO Analysis sidebar to check: keyword density and placement, estimated word count vs. competing pages for the target keyword, readability score, and suggested internal linking opportunities (the platform scans your existing content for relevant pages to link to). The AI generator automatically incorporates the target keyword in the title, introduction, and strategically throughout the content — you can adjust keyword placement in the editor before publishing.</p>`,
