    excerpt: "A complete list of all available platform integrations, what each one enables, and how to connect them from the Settings panel.",
    content: `<h2>Marketing and Analytics Integrations</h2><p><strong>Google Search Console</strong>: Import organic search performance data — clicks, impressions, CTR, and ranking positions from Google directly. <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong>: Import traffic and conversion data to supplement our platform's own analytics. <strong>Google Ads</strong>: Connect your PPC data to compare paid and organic keyword performance side by side.</p><h2>CRM and Email Integrations</h2><p><strong>HubSpot</strong>: Sync leads bidirectionally — leads captured through your forms appear in HubSpot, and HubSpot deals update lead statuses in our platform. <strong>Salesforce</strong>: Sync qualified leads to Salesforce opportunities for your sales team's pipeline management. <strong>Mailchimp</strong>: Sync your lead list to Mailchimp for campaigns you manage in Mailchimp while tracking performance in our platform.</p><h2>Connecting Integrations</h2><p>All integrations are configured in Settings → Integrations. Each integration requires OAuth authentication or API key configuration — follow the setup wizard for each integration. Integrations can be disconnected at any time without losing data already imported to the platform. Reconnecting an integration after disconnection will re-sync current data but may not restore historical data from the disconnection period.</p>`,
