    content: `<h2>API Access</h2><p>The platform API allows programmatic access to your SEO and marketing data for custom reporting, data warehouse integration, or building custom tools. Generate your API key in Settings → Developer → API Keys. The REST API supports GET endpoints for: keywords and rankings, backlinks, leads and contacts, campaign performance, and analytics summary data. Full API documentation is available at the developer docs link in Settings → Developer.</p><h2>Webhook Configuration</h2><p>Webhooks push data to your specified endpoint URL in real-time when specific events occur. Configure webhooks in Settings → Developer → Webhooks. Supported events include: new lead created, lead status changed, new backlink detected (above your configured DA threshold), keyword ranking change (above your configured position change threshold), and campaign sent. Each webhook sends a JSON payload to your endpoint URL with event details.</p><h2>Rate Limits and Best Practices</h2><p>API requests are rate-limited to 100 requests per minute per API key. For bulk data access, use the data export endpoints rather than individual resource endpoints — exports handle rate limiting internally and deliver complete datasets efficiently. Implement exponential backoff in your API clients to handle rate limit responses gracefully. Store API keys securely (environment variables, not hardcoded in application code) and generate new keys immediately if you suspect a key has been compromised.</p>`,
