    content: `<h2>Creating Lead Forms</h2><p>Navigate to Leads → Lead Forms → Create Form. Configure your form: select which fields to include (name, email, company, phone, custom fields), set required vs. optional fields, customize the submit button text, and configure the post-submission action (redirect to a thank you page URL, or show an inline success message). Forms support custom CSS for styling consistency with your website's design system.</p><h2>Embedding Forms on Your Website</h2><p>After creating a form, copy the embed code from the form's settings. The embed code is a JavaScript snippet that renders the form in any HTML container on your website. Paste the embed code into your website's HTML where you want the form to appear — compatible with all major website platforms (WordPress, Webflow, Wix, Shopify, and custom HTML sites). The form automatically submits to our platform and creates a lead record — no additional backend configuration required.</p><h2>Form Automation and Lead Routing</h2><p>Configure automation triggered by form submissions: automatically tag leads from a specific form (e.g., tag "contact-form" vs. "webinar-signup" based on which form captured the lead), add them to a specific email nurture sequence, and assign to a specific team member in the leads module. Lead routing rules can also send real-time email notifications to your sales team when a form submission matches high-value criteria (e.g., company size above a threshold or specific industry selection).</p>`,
